# Per-mode model selection via --config and rlx-config.yaml

## Overview

Introduce a per-mode model configuration mechanism. A new `--config <path>` CLI
flag (valid for `--plan`, `--task`, and `--review`) points at an optional
`rlx-config.yaml` file whose top-level keys are the modes (`plan`, `task`,
`review`) and whose only nested field today is `model`. When `--config` is
omitted, rlx auto-discovers `rlx-config.yaml` in the directory of the plan or
task file (the auto-discovery is plan/task-relative; `--review` honors only
explicit `--config`). The TOML config (`.rlx/config.toml`) gains explicit
`plan_model`, `task_model`, `review_model` fields, each defaulting to
`"opus4.7"`. The YAML overrides whichever subset it specifies; everything
absent falls through to TOML, then to the in-code default. Each mode wires
its executor(s) to the model that resolves for that mode.

