    `claude_model`-based executor wiring with mode-specific resolution. Replace
    `_build_review_executor` with a small helper that always builds the
    review executor when `review_model != task_model` (the conditional logic
    is preserved but driven by the new field names).
  - `tests/test_config.py` — new tests for YAML parsing, TOML+YAML merge
    precedence, defaults, missing/unreadable YAML.
  - `tests/test_cli.py` — update existing tests that reference
    `claude_model`/`review_model` semantics to the new field names; add tests
    for `--config` flag plumbing and auto-discovery.
  - `README.md`, `docs/reference/02-config.md`, `docs/reference/03-cli.md` —
    documentation for the new flag, YAML format, and field rename.
- Related patterns:
  - Manual YAML-shape parsing already exists for agent frontmatter in
    `src/rlx/processor/agents.py` (`_parse_frontmatter`). The new YAML loader
    follows the same hand-rolled style (no PyYAML dependency); the accepted
    shape is intentionally restricted to two indentation levels and the keys
    listed below.
  - TOML loading already cleanly merges over dataclass defaults via the field
    sets `_STR_FIELDS`, `_INT_FIELDS`, etc. Add `plan_model`, `task_model`,
    `review_model` to `_STR_FIELDS` (and drop `claude_model`).
- Dependencies: none added. Continue using stdlib only.

