### Task 2: YAML loader for rlx-config.yaml

**Files:**
- Modify: `src/rlx/config.py`
- Modify: `tests/test_config.py`

- [ ] Add a `YamlOverrides` dataclass with optional fields
      `plan_model: str | None`, `task_model: str | None`,
      `review_model: str | None` (all `None` means "no override").
- [ ] Add `parse_yaml_overrides(text: str) -> YamlOverrides` that hand-parses
      the restricted shape:
      ```yaml
      plan:
        model: <value>
      task:
        model: <value>
      review:
        model: <value>
      ```
      Tolerated: blank lines, `# ...` comments, surrounding whitespace,
      single/double quotes around the value. Unknown top-level keys and
      unknown nested keys are ignored (no error). Unparseable / malformed
      YAML raises `ValueError("invalid rlx-config.yaml: <reason>")`.
- [ ] Add `load_yaml_config(path: Path) -> YamlOverrides`. Raises
      `FileNotFoundError` when missing, `ValueError` when malformed.
- [ ] Add `apply_yaml_overrides(cfg: Config, overrides: YamlOverrides) ->
      None` that mutates `cfg` in place: each non-`None` field replaces
      the corresponding `Config.<x>_model`.
- [ ] Add `find_yaml_config(start_dir: Path) -> Path | None` that returns
      `start_dir / "rlx-config.yaml"` if it exists, else `None`. (No
      ancestor walk; rule from the prompt: look in the directory of the
      plan/task file.)
- [ ] write tests for this task: parser happy paths (all three modes; one
